401InspectorStubFrontend::InspectorStubFrontend(Page& inspectedPage, RefPtr<DOMWindow>&& frontendWindow)
402 : InspectorFrontendClientLocal(&inspectedPage.inspectorController(), frontendWindow->document()->page(), makeUnique<InspectorFrontendClientLocal::Settings>())
403 , m_frontendWindow(frontendWindow.copyRef())
404{
405 ASSERT_ARG(frontendWindow, frontendWindow);
406
407 frontendPage()->inspectorController().setInspectorFrontendClient(this);
408 inspectedPage.inspectorController().connectFrontend(*this);
409}
410
411InspectorStubFrontend::~InspectorStubFrontend()
412{
413 closeWindow();
414}
415
416void InspectorStubFrontend::closeWindow()
417{
418 if (!m_frontendWindow)
419 return;
420
421 frontendPage()->inspectorController().setInspectorFrontendClient(nullptr);
422 inspectedPage()->inspectorController().disconnectFrontend(*this);
423
424 m_frontendWindow->close();
425 m_frontendWindow = nullptr;
426}

430 frontendAPIDispatcher().dispatchMessageAsync(message);

433static bool markerTypeFrom(const String& markerType, DocumentMarker::MarkerType& result)
434{
435 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "spelling"))
436 result = DocumentMarker::Spelling;
437 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "grammar"))
438 result = DocumentMarker::Grammar;
439 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "textmatch"))
440 result = DocumentMarker::TextMatch;
441 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "replacement"))
442 result = DocumentMarker::Replacement;
443 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "correctionindicator"))
444 result = DocumentMarker::CorrectionIndicator;
445 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "rejectedcorrection"))
446 result = DocumentMarker::RejectedCorrection;
447 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "autocorrected"))
448 result = DocumentMarker::Autocorrected;
449 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "spellcheckingexemption"))
450 result = DocumentMarker::SpellCheckingExemption;
451 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "deletedautocorrection"))
452 result = DocumentMarker::DeletedAutocorrection;
453 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "dictationalternatives"))
454 result = DocumentMarker::DictationAlternatives;
455#if ENABLE(TELEPHONE_NUMBER_DETECTION)
456 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "telephonenumber"))
457 result = DocumentMarker::TelephoneNumber;
458#endif
459 else
460 return false;
461
462 return true;
463}
464
465static bool markerTypesFrom(const String& markerType, OptionSet<DocumentMarker::MarkerType>& result)
466{
467 DocumentMarker::MarkerType singularResult;
468
469 if (markerType.isEmpty() || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(markerType, "all"))
470 result = DocumentMarker::allMarkers();
471 else if (markerTypeFrom(markerType, singularResult))
472 result = singularResult;
473 else
474 return false;
475
476 return true;
477}

503void Internals::resetToConsistentState(Page& page)
504{
505 page.setPageScaleFactor(1, IntPoint(0, 0));
506 page.setPagination(Pagination());
507 page.setPaginationLineGridEnabled(false);
508
509 page.setDefersLoading(false);
510
511 page.mainFrame().setTextZoomFactor(1.0f);
512
513 page.setCompositingPolicyOverride(WebCore::CompositingPolicy::Normal);
514
515 FrameView* mainFrameView = page.mainFrame().view();
516 if (mainFrameView) {
517 page.setHeaderHeight(0);
518 page.setFooterHeight(0);
519 page.setTopContentInset(0);
520 mainFrameView->setUseFixedLayout(false);
521 mainFrameView->setFixedLayoutSize(IntSize());
522 mainFrameView->enableFixedWidthAutoSizeMode(false, { });
523#if USE(COORDINATED_GRAPHICS)
524 mainFrameView->setFixedVisibleContentRect(IntRect());
525#endif
526 if (auto* backing = mainFrameView->tiledBacking())
527 backing->setTileSizeUpdateDelayDisabledForTesting(false);
528 }
529
530 WTF::clearDefaultPortForProtocolMapForTesting();
531 overrideUserPreferredLanguages(Vector<String>());
532 WebCore::DeprecatedGlobalSettings::setUsesOverlayScrollbars(false);
533 WebCore::DeprecatedGlobalSettings::setUsesMockScrollAnimator(false);
534 if (!page.mainFrame().editor().isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled())
535 page.mainFrame().editor().toggleContinuousSpellChecking();
536 if (page.mainFrame().editor().isOverwriteModeEnabled())
537 page.mainFrame().editor().toggleOverwriteModeEnabled();
538 page.mainFrame().loader().clearTestingOverrides();
539 page.applicationCacheStorage().setDefaultOriginQuota(ApplicationCacheStorage::noQuota());
540#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
541 page.group().captionPreferences().setTestingMode(true);
542 page.group().captionPreferences().setCaptionDisplayMode(CaptionUserPreferences::ForcedOnly);
543 page.group().captionPreferences().setCaptionsStyleSheetOverride(emptyString());
544 page.group().captionPreferences().setTestingMode(false);
545 PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().resetHaveEverRegisteredAsNowPlayingApplicationForTesting();
546 PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().resetRestrictions();
547 PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().setWillIgnoreSystemInterruptions(true);
548#endif
549#if ENABLE(VIDEO) || ENABLE(WEB_AUDIO)
550 PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().setIsPlayingToAutomotiveHeadUnit(false);
551#endif
552#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY)
553 AXObjectCache::setEnhancedUserInterfaceAccessibility(false);
554 AXObjectCache::disableAccessibility();
555#endif
556
557 MockPageOverlayClient::singleton().uninstallAllOverlays();
558
559#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
560 MockContentFilterSettings::reset();
561#endif
562
563#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
564 page.setMockMediaPlaybackTargetPickerEnabled(true);
565 page.setMockMediaPlaybackTargetPickerState(emptyString(), MediaPlaybackTargetContext::MockState::Unknown);
566#endif
567
568#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
569 MediaResourceLoader::recordResponsesForTesting();
570#endif
571
572 page.setShowAllPlugins(false);
573 page.setLowPowerModeEnabledOverrideForTesting(std::nullopt);
574 page.setOutsideViewportThrottlingEnabledForTesting(false);
575
576#if USE(QUICK_LOOK)
577 MockPreviewLoaderClient::singleton().setPassword("");
578 LegacyPreviewLoader::setClientForTesting(nullptr);
579#endif
580
581 printContextForTesting() = nullptr;
582
583#if USE(LIBWEBRTC)
584 auto& rtcProvider = page.libWebRTCProvider();
585 WebCore::useRealRTCPeerConnectionFactory(rtcProvider);
586 rtcProvider.disableNonLocalhostConnections();
587 LibWebRTCProvider::setH264HardwareEncoderAllowed(true);
588 RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().setWebRTCH265CodecEnabled(true);
589 page.settings().setWebRTCEncryptionEnabled(true);
590#endif
591
592 page.setFullscreenAutoHideDuration(0_s);
593 page.setFullscreenInsets({ });
594 page.setFullscreenControlsHidden(false);
595
596 MediaEngineConfigurationFactory::disableMock();
597
598#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
599 page.settings().setInterruptAudioOnPageVisibilityChangeEnabled(false);
600 WebCore::MediaRecorder::setCustomPrivateRecorderCreator(nullptr);
601#endif
602
603 HTMLCanvasElement::setMaxPixelMemoryForTesting(0); // This means use the default value.
604 DOMWindow::overrideTransientActivationDurationForTesting(std::nullopt);
605
606#if PLATFORM(IOS)
607 RenderThemeIOS::setContentSizeCategory(kCTFontContentSizeCategoryL);
608#endif
609}

611Internals::Internals(Document& document)
612 : ContextDestructionObserver(&document)
613#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
614 , m_orientationNotifier(0)
615#endif
616{
617#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
618 if (document.page())
619 document.page()->group().captionPreferences().setTestingMode(true);
620#endif
621
622#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
623 if (document.page())
624 document.page()->setMockMediaPlaybackTargetPickerEnabled(true);
625#endif
626
627 if (contextDocument() && contextDocument()->frame()) {
628 setAutomaticSpellingCorrectionEnabled(true);
629 setAutomaticQuoteSubstitutionEnabled(false);
630 setAutomaticDashSubstitutionEnabled(false);
631 setAutomaticLinkDetectionEnabled(false);
632 setAutomaticTextReplacementEnabled(true);
633 }
634
635 setConsoleMessageListener(nullptr);
636
637#if ENABLE(APPLE_PAY)
638 auto* frame = document.frame();
639 if (frame && frame->page() && frame->isMainFrame()) {
640 auto mockPaymentCoordinator = new MockPaymentCoordinator(*frame->page());
641 frame->page()->setPaymentCoordinator(makeUnique<PaymentCoordinator>(*mockPaymentCoordinator));
642 }
643#endif
644
645#if PLATFORM(COCOA) && ENABLE(WEB_AUDIO)
646 AudioDestinationCocoa::createOverride = nullptr;
647#endif
648
649#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
650 SystemBatteryStatusTestingOverrides::singleton().setHasAC(std::nullopt);
651 SystemBatteryStatusTestingOverrides::singleton().setHasBattery(std::nullopt);
652#endif
653
654#if ENABLE(VP9) && PLATFORM(COCOA)
655 VP9TestingOverrides::singleton().setHardwareDecoderDisabled(std::nullopt);
656 VP9TestingOverrides::singleton().setVP9ScreenSizeAndScale(std::nullopt);
657#endif
658}

660Document* Internals::contextDocument() const

665Frame* Internals::frame() const

672InternalSettings* Internals::settings() const
673{
674 Document* document = contextDocument();
675 if (!document)
676 return nullptr;
677 Page* page = document->page();
678 if (!page)
679 return nullptr;
680 return InternalSettings::from(page);
681}
682
683unsigned Internals::inflightBeaconsCount() const
684{
685 auto* document = contextDocument();
686 if (!document)
687 return 0;
688
689 auto* window = document->domWindow();
690 if (!window)
691 return 0;
692
693 auto* navigator = window->optionalNavigator();
694 if (!navigator)
695 return 0;
696
697 return NavigatorBeacon::from(*navigator)->inflightBeaconsCount();
698}

704
705ExceptionOr<bool> Internals::areSVGAnimationsPaused() const
706{
707 auto* document = contextDocument();
708 if (!document)
709 return Exception { InvalidAccessError, "No context document"_s };
710
711 if (!document->svgExtensions())
712 return Exception { NotFoundError, "No SVG animations"_s };
713
714 return document->accessSVGExtensions().areAnimationsPaused();
715}
716
717ExceptionOr<double> Internals::svgAnimationsInterval(SVGSVGElement& element) const
718{
719 auto* document = contextDocument();
720 if (!document)
721 return 0;
722
723 if (!document->svgExtensions())
724 return 0;
725
726 if (document->accessSVGExtensions().areAnimationsPaused())
727 return 0;
728
729 return element.timeContainer().animationFrameDelay().value();
730}

1246static unsigned deferredStyleRulesCountForList(const Vector<RefPtr<StyleRuleBase>>& childRules)
1247{
1248 unsigned count = 0;
1249 for (auto rule : childRules) {
1250 if (is<StyleRule>(rule)) {
1251 auto* cssRule = downcast<StyleRule>(rule.get());
1252 if (!cssRule->propertiesWithoutDeferredParsing())
1253 count++;
1254 continue;
1255 }
1256
1257 StyleRuleGroup* groupRule = nullptr;
1258 if (is<StyleRuleMedia>(rule))
1259 groupRule = downcast<StyleRuleMedia>(rule.get());
1260 else if (is<StyleRuleSupports>(rule))
1261 groupRule = downcast<StyleRuleSupports>(rule.get());
1262 if (!groupRule)
1263 continue;
1264
1265 auto* groupChildRules = groupRule->childRulesWithoutDeferredParsing();
1266 if (!groupChildRules)
1267 continue;
1268
1269 count += deferredStyleRulesCountForList(*groupChildRules);
1270 }
1271
1272 return count;
1273}
1274
1275unsigned Internals::deferredStyleRulesCount(StyleSheet& styleSheet)
1276{
1277 return deferredStyleRulesCountForList(downcast<CSSStyleSheet>(styleSheet).contents().childRules());
1278}
1279
1280static unsigned deferredGroupRulesCountForList(const Vector<RefPtr<StyleRuleBase>>& childRules)
1281{
1282 unsigned count = 0;
1283 for (auto rule : childRules) {
1284 StyleRuleGroup* groupRule = nullptr;
1285 if (is<StyleRuleMedia>(rule))
1286 groupRule = downcast<StyleRuleMedia>(rule.get());
1287 else if (is<StyleRuleSupports>(rule))
1288 groupRule = downcast<StyleRuleSupports>(rule.get());
1289 if (!groupRule)
1290 continue;
1291
1292 auto* groupChildRules = groupRule->childRulesWithoutDeferredParsing();
1293 if (!groupChildRules)
1294 count++;
1295 else
1296 count += deferredGroupRulesCountForList(*groupChildRules);
1297 }
1298 return count;
1299}

1306static unsigned deferredKeyframesRulesCountForList(const Vector<RefPtr<StyleRuleBase>>& childRules)
1307{
1308 unsigned count = 0;
1309 for (auto rule : childRules) {
1310 if (is<StyleRuleKeyframes>(rule)) {
1311 auto* cssRule = downcast<StyleRuleKeyframes>(rule.get());
1312 if (!cssRule->keyframesWithoutDeferredParsing())
1313 count++;
1314 continue;
1315 }
1316
1317 StyleRuleGroup* groupRule = nullptr;
1318 if (is<StyleRuleMedia>(rule))
1319 groupRule = downcast<StyleRuleMedia>(rule.get());
1320 else if (is<StyleRuleSupports>(rule))
1321 groupRule = downcast<StyleRuleSupports>(rule.get());
1322 if (!groupRule)
1323 continue;
1324
1325 auto* groupChildRules = groupRule->childRulesWithoutDeferredParsing();
1326 if (!groupChildRules)
1327 continue;
1328
1329 count += deferredKeyframesRulesCountForList(*groupChildRules);
1330 }
1331
1332 return count;
1333}

1386void Internals::setEventThrottlingBehaviorOverride(std::optional<EventThrottlingBehavior> value)
1387{
1388 Document* document = contextDocument();
1389 if (!document || !document->page())
1390 return;
1391
1392 if (!value) {
1393 document->page()->setEventThrottlingBehaviorOverride(std::nullopt);
1394 return;
1395 }
1396
1397 switch (value.value()) {
1398 case Internals::EventThrottlingBehavior::Responsive:
1399 document->page()->setEventThrottlingBehaviorOverride(WebCore::EventThrottlingBehavior::Responsive);
1400 break;
1401 case Internals::EventThrottlingBehavior::Unresponsive:
1402 document->page()->setEventThrottlingBehaviorOverride(WebCore::EventThrottlingBehavior::Unresponsive);
1403 break;
1404 }
1405}

1407std::optional<Internals::EventThrottlingBehavior> Internals::eventThrottlingBehaviorOverride() const
1408{
1409 Document* document = contextDocument();
1410 if (!document || !document->page())
1411 return std::nullopt;
1412
1413 auto behavior = document->page()->eventThrottlingBehaviorOverride();
1414 if (!behavior)
1415 return std::nullopt;
1416
1417 switch (behavior.value()) {
1418 case WebCore::EventThrottlingBehavior::Responsive:
1419 return Internals::EventThrottlingBehavior::Responsive;
1420 case WebCore::EventThrottlingBehavior::Unresponsive:
1421 return Internals::EventThrottlingBehavior::Unresponsive;
1422 }
1423
1424 return std::nullopt;
1425}

1462ExceptionOr<Vector<String>> Internals::formControlStateOfPreviousHistoryItem()
1463{

1465 if (!mainItem)
1466 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };

1468 if (mainItem->target() != uniqueName && !mainItem->childItemWithTarget(uniqueName))

1473ExceptionOr<void> Internals::setFormControlStateOfPreviousHistoryItem(const Vector<String>& state)
1474{

1476 if (!mainItem)
1477 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1478 String uniqueName = frame()->tree().uniqueName();
1479 if (mainItem->target() == uniqueName)
1480 mainItem->setDocumentState(state);
1481 else if (HistoryItem* subItem = mainItem->childItemWithTarget(uniqueName))
1482 subItem->setDocumentState(state);
1483 else
1484 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1485 return { };
1486}

1868ExceptionOr<void> Internals::scrollBySimulatingWheelEvent(Element& element, double deltaX, double deltaY)
1869{
1870 Document* document = contextDocument();
1871 if (!document || !document->view())
1872 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1873
1874 if (!element.renderBox())
1875 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1876
1877 RenderBox& box = *element.renderBox();
1878 ScrollableArea* scrollableArea;
1879
1880 if (&element == document->scrollingElementForAPI()) {
1881 FrameView* frameView = box.frame().mainFrame().view();
1882 if (!frameView || !frameView->isScrollable())
1883 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1884
1885 scrollableArea = frameView;
1886 } else {
1887 if (!box.canBeScrolledAndHasScrollableArea())
1888 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1889
1890 ASSERT(box.layer());
1891 scrollableArea = box.layer()->scrollableArea();
1892 }
1893
1894 if (!scrollableArea)
1895 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1896
1897 auto scrollingNodeID = scrollableArea->scrollingNodeID();
1898 if (!scrollingNodeID)
1899 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1900
1901 auto page = document->page();
1902 if (!page)
1903 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1904
1905 auto scrollingCoordinator = page->scrollingCoordinator();
1906 if (!scrollingCoordinator)
1907 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
1908
1909 scrollingCoordinator->scrollBySimulatingWheelEventForTesting(scrollingNodeID, FloatSize(deltaX, deltaY));
1910
1911 return { };
1912}

2011ExceptionOr<String> Internals::configurationForViewport(float devicePixelRatio, int deviceWidth, int deviceHeight, int availableWidth, int availableHeight)
2012{
2013 Document* document = contextDocument();
2014 if (!document || !document->page())
2015 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
2016
2017 const int defaultLayoutWidthForNonMobilePages = 980;
2018
2019 ViewportArguments arguments = document->page()->viewportArguments();
2020 ViewportAttributes attributes = computeViewportAttributes(arguments, defaultLayoutWidthForNonMobilePages, deviceWidth, deviceHeight, devicePixelRatio, IntSize(availableWidth, availableHeight));
2021 restrictMinimumScaleFactorToViewportSize(attributes, IntSize(availableWidth, availableHeight), devicePixelRatio);
2022 restrictScaleFactorToInitialScaleIfNotUserScalable(attributes);
2023
2024 // FIXME: Using fixed precision here because of test results that contain numbers with specific precision. Would be nice to update the test results and move to default formatting.
2025 return makeString("viewport size ", FormattedNumber::fixedPrecision(attributes.layoutSize.width()), 'x', FormattedNumber::fixedPrecision(attributes.layoutSize.height()), " scale ", FormattedNumber::fixedPrecision(attributes.initialScale), " with limits [", FormattedNumber::fixedPrecision(attributes.minimumScale), ", ", FormattedNumber::fixedPrecision(attributes.maximumScale), "] and userScalable ", (attributes.userScalable ? "true" : "false"));
2026}

2302// FIXME: Remove the document argument. It is almost always the same as
2303// contextDocument(), with the exception of a few tests that pass a
2304// different document, and could just make the call through another Internals
2305// instance instead.
2306ExceptionOr<RefPtr<NodeList>> Internals::nodesFromRect(Document& document, int centerX, int centerY, unsigned topPadding, unsigned rightPadding, unsigned bottomPadding, unsigned leftPadding, bool ignoreClipping, bool allowUserAgentShadowContent, bool allowChildFrameContent) const
2307{
2308 if (!document.frame() || !document.frame()->view())
2309 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
2310
2311 Frame* frame = document.frame();
2312 FrameView* frameView = document.view();
2313 RenderView* renderView = document.renderView();
2314 if (!renderView)
2315 return nullptr;
2316
2317 document.updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
2318
2319 float zoomFactor = frame->pageZoomFactor();
2320 LayoutPoint point(centerX * zoomFactor + frameView->scrollX(), centerY * zoomFactor + frameView->scrollY());
2321
2322 OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::CollectMultipleElements };
2323 if (ignoreClipping)
2324 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::IgnoreClipping);
2325 if (!allowUserAgentShadowContent)
2326 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent);
2327 if (allowChildFrameContent)
2328 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::AllowChildFrameContent);
2329
2330 HitTestRequest request(hitType);
2331
2332 auto hitTestResult = [&] {
2333 auto size = LayoutSize { leftPadding + rightPadding + 1, topPadding + bottomPadding + 1 };
2334 if (size.isEmpty())
2335 return HitTestResult { point };
2336 auto adjustedPosition = LayoutPoint { flooredIntPoint(point) } - LayoutSize { leftPadding, topPadding };
2337 return HitTestResult { LayoutRect { adjustedPosition, size } };
2338 }();
2339 // When ignoreClipping is false, this method returns null for coordinates outside of the viewport.
2340 if (!request.ignoreClipping() && !hitTestResult.hitTestLocation().intersects(LayoutRect { frameView->visibleContentRect() }))
2341 return nullptr;
2342
2343 document.hitTest(request, hitTestResult);
2344 auto matches = WTF::map(hitTestResult.listBasedTestResult(), [](const auto& node) { return node.copyRef(); });
2345 return RefPtr<NodeList> { StaticNodeList::create(WTFMove(matches)) };
2346}

2348class GetCallerCodeBlockFunctor {
2349public:
2350 GetCallerCodeBlockFunctor()
2351 : m_iterations(0)
2352 , m_codeBlock(0)
2353 {
2354 }
2355
2356 StackVisitor::Status operator()(StackVisitor& visitor) const
2357 {
2358 ++m_iterations;
2359 if (m_iterations < 2)
2360 return StackVisitor::Continue;
2361
2362 m_codeBlock = visitor->codeBlock();
2363 return StackVisitor::Done;
2364 }
2365
2366 CodeBlock* codeBlock() const { return m_codeBlock; }
2367
2368private:
2369 mutable int m_iterations;
2370 mutable CodeBlock* m_codeBlock;
2371};

2373String Internals::parserMetaData(JSC::JSValue code)
2374{
2375 auto& vm = contextDocument()->vm();
2376 auto callFrame = vm.topCallFrame;
2377 auto* globalObject = callFrame->lexicalGlobalObject(vm);
2378
2379 ScriptExecutable* executable;
2380 if (!code || code.isNull() || code.isUndefined()) {
2381 GetCallerCodeBlockFunctor iter;
2382 callFrame->iterate(vm, iter);
2383 executable = iter.codeBlock()->ownerExecutable();
2384 } else if (code.isCallable(vm))
2385 executable = JSC::jsCast<JSFunction*>(code.toObject(globalObject))->jsExecutable();
2386 else
2387 return String();
2388
2389 const char* prefix = "";
2390 String functionName;
2391 const char* suffix = "";
2392
2393 if (executable->isFunctionExecutable()) {
2394 prefix = "function \"";
2395 functionName = static_cast<FunctionExecutable*>(executable)->ecmaName().string();
2396 suffix = "\"";
2397 } else if (executable->isEvalExecutable())
2398 prefix = "eval";
2399 else if (executable->isModuleProgramExecutable())
2400 prefix = "module";
2401 else if (executable->isProgramExecutable())
2402 prefix = "program";
2403 else
2404 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2405
2406 return makeString(prefix, functionName, suffix, " { ",
2407 executable->firstLine(), ':', executable->startColumn(), " - ",
2408 executable->lastLine(), ':', executable->endColumn(), " }");
2409}

2580static ExceptionOr<FindOptions> parseFindOptions(const Vector<String>& optionList)
2581{
2582 const struct {
2583 const char* name;
2584 FindOptionFlag value;
2585 } flagList[] = {
2586 {"CaseInsensitive", CaseInsensitive},
2587 {"AtWordStarts", AtWordStarts},
2588 {"TreatMedialCapitalAsWordStart", TreatMedialCapitalAsWordStart},
2589 {"Backwards", Backwards},
2590 {"WrapAround", WrapAround},
2591 {"StartInSelection", StartInSelection},
2592 {"DoNotRevealSelection", DoNotRevealSelection},
2593 {"AtWordEnds", AtWordEnds},
2594 {"DoNotTraverseFlatTree", DoNotTraverseFlatTree},
2595 };
2596 FindOptions result;
2597 for (auto& option : optionList) {
2598 bool found = false;
2599 for (auto& flag : flagList) {
2600 if (flag.name == option) {
2601 result.add(flag.value);
2602 found = true;
2603 break;
2604 }
2605 }
2606 if (!found)
2607 return Exception { SyntaxError };
2608 }
2609 return result;
2610}

2912ExceptionOr<ScrollableArea*> Internals::scrollableAreaForNode(Node* node) const
2913{
2914 if (!node)
2915 node = contextDocument();
2916
2917 if (!node)
2918 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
2919
2920 auto nodeRef = makeRef(*node);
2921 nodeRef->document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
2922
2923 ScrollableArea* scrollableArea = nullptr;
2924 if (is<Document>(nodeRef)) {
2925 auto* frameView = downcast<Document>(nodeRef.get()).view();
2926 if (!frameView)
2927 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
2928
2929 scrollableArea = frameView;
2930 } else if (node == nodeRef->document().scrollingElement()) {
2931 auto* frameView = nodeRef->document().view();
2932 if (!frameView)
2933 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
2934
2935 scrollableArea = frameView;
2936 } else if (is<Element>(nodeRef)) {
2937 auto& element = downcast<Element>(nodeRef.get());
2938 if (!element.renderBox())
2939 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
2940
2941 auto& renderBox = *element.renderBox();
2942 if (!renderBox.canBeScrolledAndHasScrollableArea())
2943 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
2944
2945 if (is<RenderListBox>(renderBox))
2946 scrollableArea = &downcast<RenderListBox>(renderBox);
2947 else {
2948 ASSERT(renderBox.layer());
2949 scrollableArea = renderBox.layer()->scrollableArea();
2950 }
2951 } else
2952 return Exception { InvalidNodeTypeError };
2953
2954 if (!scrollableArea)
2955 return Exception { InvalidNodeTypeError };
2956
2957 return scrollableArea;
2958}

2960ExceptionOr<String> Internals::scrollbarOverlayStyle(Node* node) const
2961{
2962 auto areaOrException = scrollableAreaForNode(node);
2963 if (areaOrException.hasException())
2964 return areaOrException.releaseException();
2965
2966 auto* scrollableArea = areaOrException.releaseReturnValue();
2967 switch (scrollableArea->scrollbarOverlayStyle()) {
2968 case ScrollbarOverlayStyleDefault:
2969 return "default"_str;
2970 case ScrollbarOverlayStyleDark:
2971 return "dark"_str;
2972 case ScrollbarOverlayStyleLight:
2973 return "light"_str;
2974 }
2975
2976 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2977 return "unknown"_str;
2978}

4269ExceptionOr<void> Internals::setMediaSessionRestrictions(const String& mediaTypeString, StringView restrictionsString)
4270{
4271 auto mediaType = mediaTypeFromString(mediaTypeString);
4272 if (mediaType == PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::None)
4273 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
4274
4275 auto restrictions = PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().restrictions(mediaType);
4276 PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().removeRestriction(mediaType, restrictions);
4277
4278 restrictions = PlatformMediaSessionManager::NoRestrictions;
4279
4280 for (StringView restrictionString : restrictionsString.split(',')) {
4281 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "concurrentplaybacknotpermitted"))
4282 restrictions |= PlatformMediaSessionManager::ConcurrentPlaybackNotPermitted;
4283 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "backgroundprocessplaybackrestricted"))
4284 restrictions |= PlatformMediaSessionManager::BackgroundProcessPlaybackRestricted;
4285 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "backgroundtabplaybackrestricted"))
4286 restrictions |= PlatformMediaSessionManager::BackgroundTabPlaybackRestricted;
4287 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "interruptedplaybacknotpermitted"))
4288 restrictions |= PlatformMediaSessionManager::InterruptedPlaybackNotPermitted;
4289 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "inactiveprocessplaybackrestricted"))
4290 restrictions |= PlatformMediaSessionManager::InactiveProcessPlaybackRestricted;
4291 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "suspendedunderlockplaybackrestricted"))
4292 restrictions |= PlatformMediaSessionManager::SuspendedUnderLockPlaybackRestricted;
4293 }
4294 PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().addRestriction(mediaType, restrictions);
4295 return { };
4296}
4297
4298ExceptionOr<String> Internals::mediaSessionRestrictions(const String& mediaTypeString) const
4299{
4300 PlatformMediaSession::MediaType mediaType = mediaTypeFromString(mediaTypeString);
4301 if (mediaType == PlatformMediaSession::MediaType::None)
4302 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
4303
4304 PlatformMediaSessionManager::SessionRestrictions restrictions = PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManager().restrictions(mediaType);
4305 if (restrictions == PlatformMediaSessionManager::NoRestrictions)
4306 return String();
4307
4308 StringBuilder builder;
4309 if (restrictions & PlatformMediaSessionManager::ConcurrentPlaybackNotPermitted)
4310 builder.append("concurrentplaybacknotpermitted");
4311 if (restrictions & PlatformMediaSessionManager::BackgroundProcessPlaybackRestricted) {
4312 if (!builder.isEmpty())
4313 builder.append(',');
4314 builder.append("backgroundprocessplaybackrestricted");
4315 }
4316 if (restrictions & PlatformMediaSessionManager::BackgroundTabPlaybackRestricted) {
4317 if (!builder.isEmpty())
4318 builder.append(',');
4319 builder.append("backgroundtabplaybackrestricted");
4320 }
4321 if (restrictions & PlatformMediaSessionManager::InterruptedPlaybackNotPermitted) {
4322 if (!builder.isEmpty())
4323 builder.append(',');
4324 builder.append("interruptedplaybacknotpermitted");
4325 }
4326 return builder.toString();
4327}
4328
4329void Internals::setMediaElementRestrictions(HTMLMediaElement& element, StringView restrictionsString)
4330{
4331 MediaElementSession::BehaviorRestrictions restrictions = element.mediaSession().behaviorRestrictions();
4332 element.mediaSession().removeBehaviorRestriction(restrictions);
4333
4334 restrictions = MediaElementSession::NoRestrictions;
4335
4336 for (StringView restrictionString : restrictionsString.split(',')) {
4337 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "norestrictions"))
4338 restrictions |= MediaElementSession::NoRestrictions;
4339 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "requireusergestureforload"))
4340 restrictions |= MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForLoad;
4341 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "requireusergestureforvideoratechange"))
4342 restrictions |= MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForVideoRateChange;
4343 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(restrictionString, "requireusergestureforfullscreen"))
4344 restrictions |= MediaElementSession::RequireUserGestureForFullscreen;

4742static void appendOffsets(StringBuilder& builder, const Vector<SnapOffset<LayoutUnit>>& snapOffsets)
4743{
4744 bool justStarting = true;
4745
4746 builder.append("{ ");
4747 for (auto& coordinate : snapOffsets) {
4748 if (!justStarting)
4749 builder.append(", ");
4750 else
4751 justStarting = false;
4752 builder.append(coordinate.offset.toUnsigned());
4753 if (coordinate.stop == ScrollSnapStop::Always)
4754 builder.append(" (always)");
4755
4756 }
4757 builder.append(" }");
4758}

4764
4765ExceptionOr<String> Internals::scrollSnapOffsets(Element& element)
4766{
4767 auto areaOrException = scrollableAreaForNode(&element);
4768 if (areaOrException.hasException())
4769 return areaOrException.releaseException();
4770
4771 auto* scrollableArea = areaOrException.releaseReturnValue();
4772 if (!scrollableArea)
4773 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
4774
4775 auto* offsetInfo = scrollableArea->snapOffsetsInfo();
4776 StringBuilder result;
4777 if (offsetInfo && !offsetInfo->horizontalSnapOffsets.isEmpty()) {
4778 result.append("horizontal = ");
4779 appendOffsets(result, offsetInfo->horizontalSnapOffsets);
4780 }
4781
4782 if (offsetInfo && !offsetInfo->verticalSnapOffsets.isEmpty()) {
4783 if (result.length())
4784 result.append(", ");
4785 result.append("vertical = ");
4786 appendOffsets(result, offsetInfo->verticalSnapOffsets);
4787 }
4788
4789 return result.toString();
4790}

4810ExceptionOr<String> Internals::pathStringWithShrinkWrappedRects(const Vector<double>& rectComponents, double radius)
4811{
4812 if (rectComponents.size() % 4)
4813 return Exception { InvalidAccessError };
4814
4815 Vector<FloatRect> rects;
4816 for (unsigned i = 0; i < rectComponents.size(); i += 4)
4817 rects.append(FloatRect(rectComponents[i], rectComponents[i + 1], rectComponents[i + 2], rectComponents[i + 3]));
4818
4819 SVGPathStringBuilder builder;
4820 PathUtilities::pathWithShrinkWrappedRects(rects, radius).apply([&builder](const PathElement& element) {
4821 switch (element.type) {
4822 case PathElement::Type::MoveToPoint:
4823 builder.moveTo(element.points[0], false, AbsoluteCoordinates);
4824 return;
4825 case PathElement::Type::AddLineToPoint:
4826 builder.lineTo(element.points[0], AbsoluteCoordinates);
4827 return;
4828 case PathElement::Type::AddQuadCurveToPoint:
4829 builder.curveToQuadratic(element.points[0], element.points[1], AbsoluteCoordinates);
4830 return;
4831 case PathElement::Type::AddCurveToPoint:
4832 builder.curveToCubic(element.points[0], element.points[1], element.points[2], AbsoluteCoordinates);
4833 return;
4834 case PathElement::Type::CloseSubpath:
4835 builder.closePath();
4836 return;
4837 }
4838 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4839 });
4840 return builder.result();
4841}

4906
4907JSValue Internals::cloneArrayBuffer(JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, JSValue buffer, JSValue srcByteOffset, JSValue srcLength)
4908{
4909 JSC::VM& vm = lexicalGlobalObject.vm();
4910 JSVMClientData* clientData = static_cast<JSVMClientData*>(vm.clientData);
4911 const Identifier& privateName = clientData->builtinNames().cloneArrayBufferPrivateName();
4912 JSValue value;
4913 PropertySlot propertySlot(value, PropertySlot::InternalMethodType::Get);
4914 lexicalGlobalObject.methodTable(vm)->getOwnPropertySlot(&lexicalGlobalObject, &lexicalGlobalObject, privateName, propertySlot);
4915 value = propertySlot.getValue(&lexicalGlobalObject, privateName);
4916 ASSERT(value.isCallable(vm));
4917
4918 JSObject* function = value.getObject();
4919 auto callData = JSC::getCallData(vm, function);
4920 ASSERT(callData.type != JSC::CallData::Type::None);
4921 MarkedArgumentBuffer arguments;
4922 arguments.append(buffer);
4923 arguments.append(srcByteOffset);
4924 arguments.append(srcLength);
4925 ASSERT(!arguments.hasOverflowed());
4926
4927 return JSC::call(&lexicalGlobalObject, function, callData, JSC::jsUndefined(), arguments);
4928}

5128ExceptionOr<void> Internals::queueTask(ScriptExecutionContext& context, const String& taskSourceName, RefPtr<VoidCallback>&& callback)
5129{
5130 auto source = taskSourceFromString(taskSourceName);
5131 if (!source)
5132 return Exception { NotSupportedError };
5133
5134 context.eventLoop().queueTask(*source, [callback = WTFMove(callback)] {
5135 callback->handleEvent();
5136 });
5137
5138 return { };
5139}
5140
5141ExceptionOr<void> Internals::queueTaskToQueueMicrotask(Document& document, const String& taskSourceName, RefPtr<VoidCallback>&& callback)
5142{
5143 auto source = taskSourceFromString(taskSourceName);
5144 if (!source)
5145 return Exception { NotSupportedError };
5146
5147 ScriptExecutionContext& context = document; // This avoids unnecessarily exporting Document::eventLoop.
5148 context.eventLoop().queueTask(*source, [movedCallback = WTFMove(callback), protectedDocument = makeRef(document)]() mutable {
5149 ScriptExecutionContext& context = protectedDocument.get();
5150 context.eventLoop().queueMicrotask([callback = WTFMove(movedCallback)] {
5151 callback->handleEvent();
5152 });
5153 });
5154
5155 return { };
5156}
5157
5158ExceptionOr<bool> Internals::hasSameEventLoopAs(WindowProxy& proxy)
5159{
5160 RefPtr<ScriptExecutionContext> context = contextDocument();
5161 if (!context || !proxy.frame())
5162 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
5163
5164 auto& proxyFrame = *proxy.frame();
5165 if (!is<Frame>(proxyFrame))
5166 return false;
5167 RefPtr<ScriptExecutionContext> proxyContext = downcast<Frame>(proxyFrame).document();
5168 if (!proxyContext)
5169 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
5170
5171 return context->eventLoop().hasSameEventLoopAs(proxyContext->eventLoop());
5172}

5385void Internals::videoSampleAvailable(MediaSample& sample)
5386{
5387 m_trackVideoSampleCount++;
5388 if (!m_nextTrackFramePromise)
5389 return;
5390
5391 auto& videoSettings = m_trackSource->settings();
5392 if (!videoSettings.width() || !videoSettings.height())
5393 return;
5394
5395 auto rgba = sample.getRGBAImageData();
5396 if (!rgba)
5397 return;
5398
5399 auto imageData = ImageData::create(rgba.releaseNonNull(), videoSettings.width(), videoSettings.height(), { { PredefinedColorSpace::SRGB } });
5400 if (!imageData.hasException())
5401 m_nextTrackFramePromise->resolve(imageData.releaseReturnValue());
5402 else
5403 m_nextTrackFramePromise->reject(imageData.exception().code());
5404 m_nextTrackFramePromise = nullptr;
5405}

5751
5752String Internals::ongoingLoadsDescriptions() const
5753{
5754 StringBuilder builder;
5755 builder.append('[');
5756 bool isStarting = true;
5757 for (auto& identifier : platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->ongoingLoads()) {
5758 if (isStarting)
5759 isStarting = false;
5760 else
5761 builder.append(',');
5762
5763 builder.append('[');
5764
5765 for (auto& info : platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->intermediateLoadInformationFromResourceLoadIdentifier(identifier))
5766 builder.append('[', (int)info.type, ",\"", info.request.url().string(), "\",\"", info.request.httpMethod(), "\",", info.response.httpStatusCode(), ']');
5767
5768 builder.append(']');
5769 }
5770 builder.append(']');
5771 return builder.toString();
5772}

6270void Internals::loadArtworkImage(String&& url, ArtworkImagePromise&& promise)
6271{
6272 if (!contextDocument()) {
6273 promise.reject(Exception { InvalidStateError, "No document." });
6274 return;
6275 }
6276 if (m_artworkImagePromise) {
6277 promise.reject(Exception { InvalidStateError, "Another download is currently pending." });
6278 return;
6279 }
6280 m_artworkImagePromise = makeUnique<ArtworkImagePromise>(WTFMove(promise));
6281 m_artworkLoader = makeUnique<ArtworkImageLoader>(*contextDocument(), url, [this](Image* image) {
6282 if (image) {
6283 auto imageData = ImageData::create(image->width(), image->height(), { { PredefinedColorSpace::SRGB } });
6284 if (!imageData.hasException())
6285 m_artworkImagePromise->resolve(imageData.releaseReturnValue());
6286 else
6287 m_artworkImagePromise->reject(imageData.exception().code());
6288 } else
6289 m_artworkImagePromise->reject(Exception { InvalidAccessError, "No image retrieved." });
6290 m_artworkImagePromise = nullptr;
6291 });
6292 m_artworkLoader->requestImageResource();
6293}

6387String Internals::dumpStyleResolvers()
6388{
6389 auto* document = contextDocument();
6390 if (!document || !document->domWindow())
6391 return { };
6392
6393 document->updateStyleIfNeeded();
6394
6395 unsigned currentIdentifier = 0;
6396 HashMap<Style::Resolver*, unsigned> resolverIdentifiers;
6397
6398 StringBuilder result;
6399
6400 auto dumpResolver = [&](auto name, auto& resolver) {
6401 auto identifier = resolverIdentifiers.ensure(&resolver, [&] {
6402 return currentIdentifier++;
6403 }).iterator->value;
6404
6405 result.append("(", name, " ");
6406 result.append("(identifier=", identifier, ") ");
6407 result.append("(author rule count=", resolver.ruleSets().authorStyle().ruleCount(), ")");
6408 result.append(")\n");
6409 };
6410
6411 dumpResolver("document resolver", document->styleScope().resolver());
6412
6413 for (auto* shadowRoot : document->inDocumentShadowRoots()) {
6414 auto* name = shadowRoot->mode() == ShadowRootMode::UserAgent ? "shadow root resolver (user agent)" : "shadow root resolver (author)";
6415 dumpResolver(name, shadowRoot->styleScope().resolver());
6416 }
6417
6418 return result.toString();
6419}

6421ExceptionOr<void> Internals::setDocumentAutoplayPolicy(Document& document, Internals::AutoplayPolicy policy)
6422{
6423 static_assert(static_cast<uint8_t>(WebCore::AutoplayPolicy::Default) == static_cast<uint8_t>(Internals::AutoplayPolicy::Default), "Internals::Default != WebCore::Default");
6424 static_assert(static_cast<uint8_t>(WebCore::AutoplayPolicy::Allow) == static_cast<uint8_t>(Internals::AutoplayPolicy::Allow), "Internals::Allow != WebCore::Allow");
6425 static_assert(static_cast<uint8_t>(WebCore::AutoplayPolicy::AllowWithoutSound) == static_cast<uint8_t>(Internals::AutoplayPolicy::AllowWithoutSound), "Internals::AllowWithoutSound != WebCore::AllowWithoutSound");
6426 static_assert(static_cast<uint8_t>(WebCore::AutoplayPolicy::Deny) == static_cast<uint8_t>(Internals::AutoplayPolicy::Deny), "Internals::Deny != WebCore::Deny");
6427
6428 auto* loader = document.loader();
6429 if (!loader)
6430 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
6431
6432 loader->setAutoplayPolicy(static_cast<WebCore::AutoplayPolicy>(policy));
6433
6434 return { };
6435}
